Valero Energy Corp Shuts All Units At Meraux Refinery After Fire - Reuters
Sunday, 22 Jul 2012 08:00pm EDT
Reuters reported that Valero Energy Corp said all units at its 125,000 barrel-per-day Meraux, Louisiana, refinery were shut following a fire early. The units will remain down while repairs are made to the crude unit and related utilities. A leaking exchanger at the refinery caught on fire at about 1:30 a.m. local time (0630 GMT) on July 22, a report filed with the U.S. National Response Center showed. The fire was extinguished on July 22 with no injuries. The refinery can process medium sour crude oil and produces premium products.Â 
